'''Yang Hyun-jun''' ({{Korean|hangul=양현준}}; born 25 May 2002) is a South Korean professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]] (or [[Defender (association football)#Wing-back|right wing-back]] if necessary) for {{Scottish football updater|Celtic}} club [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]] and the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]].

==Club career==

===Gangwon FC===
Yang joined [[Gangwon FC]] just after graduating from high school in 2021.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.yna.co.kr/view/AKR20210107131400007 |script-title=ko:강원FC, 박상혁·양현준·김기환·김대우 '신인 계약' |language=ko |publisher=Yonhap News Agency |date=2021-01-07 |access-date=2024-03-28}}</ref> He was evaluated as the best [[K League]] talent by winning four Young Player of the Month awards and the [[K League Young Player of the Year Award|Young Player of the Year award]] in his second professional season.<ref name="awards">{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/kr/%EB%89%B4%EC%8A%A4/goal-live-%E1%84%8B%E1%85%A3%E1%86%BC%E1%84%92%E1%85%A7%E1%86%AB%E1%84%8C%E1%85%AE%E1%86%AB-k%E1%84%85%E1%85%B5%E1%84%80%E1%85%B31-%E1%84%8B%E1%85%A7%E1%86%BC%E1%84%91%E1%85%B3%E1%86%AF%E1%84%85%E1%85%A6%E1%84%8B%E1%85%B5%E1%84%8B%E1%85%A5%E1%84%89%E1%85%A1%E1%86%BC-%E1%84%89%E1%85%AE%E1%84%89%E1%85%A1%E1%86%BC--%E1%84%89%E1%85%B5%E1%84%8C%E1%85%B3%E1%86%AB-%E1%84%8C%E1%85%A5%E1%86%AB%E1%84%81%E1%85%A1%E1%84%8C%E1%85%B5%E1%84%86%E1%85%A1%E1%86%AB-%E1%84%92%E1%85%A2%E1%84%83%E1%85%A9-%E1%84%87%E1%85%A1%E1%86%AE%E1%84%8B%E1%85%B3%E1%86%AF-%E1%84%8C%E1%85%AE%E1%86%AF-%E1%84%86%E1%85%A9%E1%86%AF%E1%84%85%E1%85%A1%E1%86%BB%E1%84%83%E1%85%A1/blt89f51b053ac17cb0 |script-title=ko:[GOAL LIVE] 양현준, K리그1 영플레이어상 수상…"시즌 전까지만 해도 받을 줄 몰랐다" |website=Goal.com |language=ko |date=2022-10-24 |access-date=2024-03-28}}</ref> He attracted Koreans with his dribbling skills during the season, especially in the [[K League All-Star Game]] against [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://sports.news.nate.com/view/20220728n33723 |script-title=ko:[인터뷰] '토트넘전 라이징스타' 양현준 "언젠간 국대로 뛰고파" |language=ko |website=Nate.com |publisher=Ilyo Shinmun |date=2022-07-28 |access-date=2024-03-28}}</ref>

===Celtic===

On 15 July 2023, Gangwon FC announced that Yang would be transferring to [[Scottish Premiership]] club [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://gangwon-fc.com/news/222109 |script-title=ko:강원FC 양현준 셀틱 이적 '한국 축구 발전 위한 대승적 결정' |language=ko |publisher=Gangwon FC |date=15 July 2023 |access-date=15 July 2023}}</ref> On 24 July, Celtic announced that Yang had signed on a five-year deal for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66288703 |title=Celtic sign Hyunjun Yang on five-year deal from Gangwon FC |publisher=BBC Sport |date=24 July 2023 |access-date=24 July 2023}}</ref> Yang made his Celtic debut in a 4–2 victory over [[Ross County F.C.|Ross County]] on 5 August. He also made his [[UEFA Champions League]] debut as a starter in a 2–1 defeat to [[SS Lazio|Lazio]] on 4 October. He scored his first goal for Celtic in a 6–0 victory over [[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]] on 12 November.

On 12 February 2025, Yang provided his first Champions League assist in a 2–1 loss to [[Bayern Munich]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://fbref.com/en/matches/b424ad1b/Celtic-Bayern-Munich-February-12-2025-Champions-League |title=Celtic vs. Bayern Munich Match Report – Wednesday February 12, 2025 (Leg 1) |publisher=FBref |access-date=2025-02-14}}</ref> On 1 March, he had come on as a 65th minute substitute against [[St Mirren F.C.|St Mirren]], and was named the Player of the Match by having two goals and one assist which broke a 2–2 tie.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.celticquicknews.co.uk/st-mirren-2-celtic-5-wham-bang-thank-you-yang/ |title=ST MIRREN 2 CELTIC 5: WHAM, BANG, THANK YOU, YANG |publisher=Celtic Quick News |date=2025-03-01 |access-date=2025-03-03}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://cdn.interfootball.co.kr/news/photo/202503/652057_729582_3222.jpg |script-title=ko:"여친 오고 더 잘한다, 집 갈 때 꽃 사가겠다"...양현준 세인트 미렌전 2골 1도움 활약 비결은 '사랑' |language=ko |publisher=InterFootball |date=2025-03-02 |access-date=2025-03-03}}</ref>

On 3 January 2026, Yang broke down [[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]' defense with his dribbling to score the opening goal, but Celtic lost 3–1 in the [[Old Firm]] derby despite his solo goal.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/742456 |title=Celtic 1-3 Rangers (Jan 3, 2026) Game Analysis |publisher=ESPN |date=2026-01-03 |access-date=2026-01-03}}</ref> On 10 May, he once again scored a goal in the Old Firm derby, and Celtic won 3–1 this time.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/cj9p1dvvyxyt |title=Scottish Premiership: Celtic 3-1 Rangers |publisher=BBC Sport |date=2026-05-10 |access-date=2026-05-17}}</ref> In the 2025–26 season, he was promoted from substitute to starter at the club, and helped them surpass the record of 55 Scottish league titles, set by Rangers.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11787/13544351/celtic-3-1-hearts-martin-oneills-side-crowned-scottish-premiership-champions-on-final-day-as-jambos-miss-out-on-historic-title |title=Celtic 3-1 Hearts: Martin O'Neill's side crowned Scottish Premiership champions on final day as Jambos miss out on historic title |publisher=Sky Sports |date=2026-05-17 |access-date=2026-05-17}}</ref> The following week, Celtic extended their contract with him until 2030.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.celticfc.com/news/2026/may/22/yang-extends-his-stay-with-celtic-until-2030/ |title=Yang extends his stay with Celtic until 2030 |publisher=Celtic F.C. |date=2026-05-23 |access-date=2026-05-23}}</ref>

==International career==
Yang was selected for the [[South Korea national football team|South Korea national team]] for the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]], playing two matches as a substitute.<ref name=soccerway/>

Yang was called up to the national team for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.goal.com/en/lists/south-korea-squad-world-cup-2026/blt15c57f5be1972d9b |title=South Korea squad World Cup 2026: Which players have made it to the showpiece in USA, Mexico and Canada? |publisher=Goal |date=2026-05-16 |access-date=2026-05-19}}</ref>

